[Outro]
So, I would just encourage everybody: never be afraid of not knowing. Never be afraid of not knowing. You know, find out. Because that’s how you get, you know, to mastership. Like, master something. And master something that people appreciate. But, you know, once you’re on top of that mountain, you have to go this way. In hip-hop everybody is like: “I’m not moving, I’m the master, I’m- I’m great, I’m dope, I’m hot, I’m here, I’ve arrived and I’m not going anywhere” and that’s where you stay stuck. On top of one… on one hill, one mountain [?]
Let’s not be mediocre in our greatness, you know what i mean?